
$Id: README,v 1.3 2006-10-03 06:17:43 jsiegel Exp $

Broadcom Dongle Host Driver.

  - Initially a pulling-apart of usbdev/hostdrv/usb-{cdc,rndis}.c to
    allow the addition of SDIO dongle support in a portable structure.

  - Subdirectory structure:
    sys -- dhd-specific source files
           (also uses headers in ../include, source in ../shared, etc)
    linux -- build directory for linux OS version

  - Overall code structure in sys:
    dhd_<os>.c	 -- bus-independent files for OS/network-stack interface 
      dhd_linux.c

    dhd_<prot>.c -- bus and OS-independent dongle message protocols
      dhd_cdc.c

    dhd_<bus>.c  -- bus-specific code, possibly os-specific pieces
      dhd_usb_linux.c
      dhd_sdio.c

Some noticeable changes expected:
  - Removing remaining linux references from bus and protocol modules.
  - Reducing host CPU overhead for SDIO by using async command interface.

#ifdef BCMINTERNAL
More information in:
  http://hwnbu-twiki.broadcom.com/bin/view/Mwgroup/DongleHostDriver
#endif
